race.comment: Tough race. SHADHAVAR (5) was a tough winner over this route last time out in BM78 grade having been run down by the talented On Display in good time prior. She draws for every chance here and can notch up another victory. SNEAKY SUNRISE (7) was good on resumption at Sandown Hillside when run down late by a handy one. Second up last time in she closed off a fast tempo to grab third behind Treasurethe Moment which reads very well. Can win. Very wary of THEBELMONTGANGSTER (16) who beat Observer at his Australian debut at Sandown Hillside, with that horse since unlucky not to win the Caulfield Guineas. Tough draw here but has plenty of upside and might just prove too smart. MARY ELIZA (15) resumes with a nice profile and draws well. Don't discount. SURFIN' BIRD (12) is on the up and will give a strong sight.
